## Accessibility

All platforms must respect user preferences:

- **Reduced motion:** Disable/minimize animations when `prefers-reduced-motion` (web) or `AccessibilityInfo.isReduceMotionEnabled` (mobile)
- **Reduced transparency:** Fall back from glass effects when enabled
- **High contrast:** Increase border weights, avoid low-contrast colors
- **Touch targets:** Minimum 44×44px on all platforms

---

## Safe Areas

| Platform | Approach |
|----------|----------|
| iOS | Native components handle it; don't add manual padding |
| Android | `useSafeAreaInsets()` from `react-native-safe-area-context` |
| Web | `env(safe-area-inset-*)` CSS, `pb-safe` Tailwind class |

---

## Quick Tests

- **Mobile:** "Would this look identical if built in Swift/Kotlin?" If no, you're overriding native behavior.
- **Web:** "Am I using modern CSS features instead of JS workarounds?" If no, check for native browser APIs.

